value: Breeds from the eastern tip of the Arctic coast of the Chukchi Peninsula and from northwestern Alaska, south to the Commander and Aleutian Islands. Winters south to Sakhalin, the KurUe Islands and coast of central California.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Mostly pelagic; nests along rocky seacoasts in cliff crevices, among boulders on beaches, and on rocky slopes with dense vegetation.
ocean, seacoasts, rocky shores, beaches, cliffs
